This paper is about a rule-based system for belief tracking in dialog systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The system also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The system's performance is evaluated based on dialog state tracking challenges, which could place it under software engineering (cs.SD) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
